<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1901-07-16T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1901-07-16T00:00:00-05:00" n="288" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d288">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Hay</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1901-07-16"><hi rend="italic">July 16,
                            1901</hi></date>.</dateline></opener>
                    <p>(Mr. Hay acknowledges Mr. Rockhill’s telegram of the 16th instant and directs
                        him to take whatever course seems to assist in bringing the negotiations to
                        a conclusion.)</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>